2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE BILL NO. 475
BY SENATOR MILLER
1 AN ACT
2 To amend and reenact Code of Civil Procedure Arts. 1201(D), 1672(C), and 3955(D) and
3 to enact Code of Civil Procedure Arts. 1201(E) and (F) and 3955(E) and (F), relative
4 to service of process; to provide with respect to service of citation; to provide
5 relative to payment of fees for service of citation in civil actions; to provide relative
6 to a statement of the initial fees and of additional fees for request for service of
7 citation; to provide relative to civil procedure; to provide relative to legal delays; to
8 provide relative to payment of fees for service of citation in certain circumstances;
9 to provide with respect to involuntary dismissal; to provide for prospective
10 application; and to provide for related matters.
11 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
12 Section 1. Code of Civil Procedure Arts. 1201(D), 1672(C), and 3955(D) are hereby
13 amended and reenacted and Code of Civil Procedure Arts. 1201(E) and (F) and 3955(E) and
14 (F) are hereby enacted to read as follows:
15 Art. 1201. Citation; waiver; delay for service
16 * * *
17 D. If not waived, a request for service of citation upon the defendant shall be
18 considered timely if requested on the defendant within the time period provided by
19 this Article and all fees specified by the clerk of court for service of citation are
20 paid within the times provided by Paragraph E of this Article, notwithstanding
21 insufficient or erroneous service.
22 E.(1) Upon receipt of a request for service of citation pursuant to this
23 Article, the clerk of court shall provide to the filing party a confirmation of
24 receipt of the request and a statement of the initial fees for the requested
