12 Art. 1672. Involuntary dismissal
13 * * *
14 C. A judgment dismissing an action without prejudice shall be rendered as
15 to a person named as a defendant for whom service has not been requested or for
16 whom all fees specified by the clerk of court for service of citation have not been
17 paid within the time times prescribed by Article 1201(C) or 3955 upon the
18 sustaining of a declinatory exception filed by such defendant, or upon contradictory
19 motion of any other party, unless good cause is shown why service could not be
20 requested or all fees specified by the clerk of court for service of citation were
21 not paid, in which case the court may order that service be effected and that a
22 specific amount of fees for service of citation be paid within a specified time.
23 * * *
24 Art. 3955. Service of petition
25 * * *
26 D. If not waived, a request for service of citation upon the defendant shall be
27 considered timely if requested on the defendant within the time period provided by
28 this Article and all fees specified by the clerk of court for service of citation are
29 paid within the times provided by this Article, notwithstanding insufficient or
30 erroneous service.
